  "text": "Basically, patients with renal impairment, particularly endstage renal disease, frequently have systemic atherosclerosis [CITATION_1] . One possibility is that higher rates of prevalence of traditional risk factors, such as advanced age, diabetes, and hypertension in the HD population may affect such high cardiovascular events [CITATION_2] .",
